title: Apple is working on 9 different M2 Mac models, developer logs reveal
content:
Apple introduced the M1 chip back in 2020. Since then, the company has been slowly ditching Intel processors and transitioning to its own silicon on the Mac lineup. It even broadened the limits of the original M1 SoC and released M1 Pro, M1 Max, and — most recently — M1 Ultra chips. This has enabled

The post Apple is working on 9 different M2 Mac models, developer logs reveal appeared first on xda-developers.
description: Third-party developer logs reveal that Apple is internally testing 9 different Mac models that are powered by 4 variants of the M2 chip.
